    {
      "id": "30e2125a2c056b199b0bff96f823de6b39e6ea8a",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 377,
        "name": "wc-checkpatch",
        "username": "hpdd-checkpatch",
        "tags": [
          "SERVICE_USER"
        ]
      },
      "date": "2018-06-14 05:08:44.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3: Code-Review-1\n\nThis change cannot be cherry-picked to master.\nPlease rebase the change locally and upload the rebased commit for review.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "8e30b7a87f5f18dc9fdfc59d113d1367a9e571bd",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2018-12-06 11:17:17.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nSee my review comments at https://lists.openwall.net/linux-ext4/2018/05/15/10 and Ted's comments at https://lists.openwall.net/linux-ext4/2018/05/24/11\n\nI think reading those comments, this patch would be more acceptable if it changed the code less and just grabbed a reference on the bitmap buffer head at mount time based on a mount option and put it into struct ext4_group_info in place of bb_bitmap (a compat macro could be added to map bb_bitmap to bb_bh->bh_data) to avoid changing a bunch of code).\n\n struct ext4_group_info {\n        :\n        unsigned long   bb_prealloc_nr;\n-#ifdef DOUBLE_CHECK\n-       void            *bb_bitmap;\n-#endif\n+       struct buffer_head *bb_bh;\n        struct rw_semaphore alloc_sem;\n        :\n }\n #define bb_bitmap bb_bh->b_data\n\nI don't think it makes sense to read all of the bitmaps at mount time, that might take 10 minutes or more if there are lots of groups and flexbg doesn't allocate the bitmaps together.  Instead, if load_bitmap mount option is used have ext4_lazyinit_thread() do this in the background (in ext4_fill_super() set first_not_zeroed = 0 and have ext4_run_li_request() load the block bitmap and save it to bb_bh if it is NULL), or in ext4_mb_init_cache() when the bitmap is first accessed if bb_bh = NULL.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "33a57b6496bb9aa70520bff62fde5236c2efd6d0",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 164,
        "name": "Shuichi Ihara",
        "email": "sihara@ddn.com",
        "username": "ihara"
      },
      "date": "2019-01-12 09:53:16.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nCan we move this forward based on Andreas's comments? Lustre Deployment standpoint, mount option can simplify and it's consistent.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "42434271d4ea313bff52e1dab5e13d3729715f44",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 337,
        "name": "Li Xi",
        "email": "lixi@ddn.com",
        "username": "LiX"
      },
      "date": "2019-11-05 14:42:47.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3: Code-Review-1\n\nIt might make sense to load the whole bitmaps during the mount process? This would 1) accelerate the mounting process in some cases and 2) accelerate the upcoming benchmarks as long as the bitmaps are not swapped out of memory?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
